      <div>
        <h2>The History of Samus</h2>
        <p class="history">Samus is an intergalactic bounty hunter from the popular <i>Metroid</i> series of Nintendo games. Samus (originally from K-2L) was raised to be a fierce warrior on Planet Zebes. The first <i>Metroid</i> game that was released in North America
          was <i>Metroid</i> for the Nintendo Entertainment System (NES) in 1987. This was an action game that featured the bounty hunter Samus Aran.</p>
        <div>
          <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metroid_(video_game)"><img class="center img-responsive" alt="Original Metroid Box Art" src="https://goo.gl/296Xb8"></a>
        </div>
        <p class="history">Samus has been featured in many different games since her original appearance in 1987. One of the most consistant appearances of Samus has been in the <i>Super Smash Brothers</i> franchise. Many of Samus' iconic moves have been carried over in
          the fighting game series. </p>
      </div>
      <div id="facts" class="well">
        <ul><b>Samus Quick Facts</b>
          <li>Debut in 1987</li>
          <li>Orange, red, and blue are her main colors</li>
          <li>Samus fires many different projectiles</li>
        </ul>
